doc.ContractDescription: WE PROPOSE TO STUDY THE CHEMICAL AND MINERALOGICAL RELATIONSHIP AMONG TYPES OF CR CHONDRITES VIA ELECTRON MICROSCOPY AND TO CONDUCT THE QUANTITATIVE ASSESSMENT OF THE PHYSICOCHEMICAL CONDITIONS OF PARENT BODY ALTERATION. CR CHONDRITES ARE IMPRINTED BY THE FULL RANGE OF AQUEOUS ALTERATION, INCLUDING CR3 AND CR1 MEMBERS AND ARE IDEAL CANDIDATES FOR UNDERSTANDING THIS PROCESS. WE PLAN TO STUDY A VARIETY OF CR CHONDRITES THAT HAVE THE POTENTIAL OF EXPOSING THE DIVERSITY OF ALTERATION FEATURES RECORDED BY THIS GROUP, INCLUDING NEWLY AVAILABLE ANTARCTIC FINDS. BASED ON OUR OBSERVATIONS, WE PLAN TO ANSWER: (1) ARE THERE SIGNS OF THERMAL METAMORPHISM AFFECTING CR CHONDRITES? (2) WHAT IS THE SEQUENCE OF ALTERATION OF MAJOR MINERALS? (3) WHAT ARE THE SOURCES AND SINKS OF ELEMENTS DURING ALTERATION? (4) WHAT ARE THE SPATIAL SCALES OF AQUEOUS ALTERATION AND (5) ARE ALL CR CHONDRITES FORMED BY DIFFERENT INTENSITIES OF ALTERATION OF MATERIALS IN CR3 CHONDRITES? OR IS VARIABILITY IN PRECURSOR MATERIALS NECESSARY TO EXPLAIN THE DIVERSITY OF ALTERATION PRODUCTS? IN THE SECOND PART OF THIS PROJECT WE WILL USE EQUILIBRIUM THERMODYNAMICS AND CHEMICAL KINETICS METHODS TO QUANTIFY AQUEOUS ALTERATION BASED ON OUR OBSERVATIONS. THIS WORK WILL LEAD TO ESTIMATES OF TEMPERATURE, PRESSURE, WATER TO ROCK RATIO, SOLUTION CHEMISTRY, AND TIME-SCALE OF ALTERATION FOR THE DIFFERENT TYPES OF CR CHONDRITES AND SPECIFIC MINERALOGICAL ASSEMBLAGES. RESULTS WILL ALSO EXPAND THE CATALOG OF ASTEROIDAL MATERIALS THAT ARE AVAILABLE FOR LABORATORY STUDY. BY EXAMINING A DIFFERENT SUITE OF CHONDRITES WE MAY PROVIDE POTENTIAL ANALOGS FOR SPECIFIC ASTEROIDS (E.G., CERES).
